  <data name="label12.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Verifying the system speaker output readability 
Tooltip: Check that the program can read the system speaker control.

Verifying the system speaker gate can be turned off and on 
Tooltip: Toggle the system speaker gate and confirm the change was accepted.

Setting the internal timer for a silent check 
Tooltip: Send a silent command to the system timer and confirm it was written.

Checking the timer is actually counting down
Tooltip: Read the timer a short time apart to see if it changes.

Reading the timer status report 
Tooltip: Ask for a status report from the timer and verify it looks normal.

Watching for the system speaker feedback signal while audio is disabled 
Tooltip: With sound turned off, watch a control line that should show the internal signal.

Confirming the feedback signal stays still when disabled
Tooltip: Turn the timer off and confirm the feedback line remains steady.

Performing a very short silent system speaker enable pulse
Tooltip: Briefly enable the system speaker for an instant that is too short to hear.

Testing two timer speeds and their reported values 
Tooltip: Set two different speeds and confirm the reported values make sense for each.

Measuring the feedback signal speed
Tooltip: Count how often the feedback line changes to estimate the internal rate.

Checking for the system speaker entry
Tooltip: Check is there a system speaker entry that's listed as "System Speaker" in system devices category of the Device Manager</value>
